gomodel:SYNGO_3072  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Over-expression of PTN/HB-GAM diminishes LTP (Fig. 2C) and deletion of the coding gene enhances LTP (Fig. 4C). A later paper by the same group shows that this might occur via modulating inhibitory synapses involved in the circuit.. Experimental description: Role of Heparin-Binding Growth-Associated Molecule (HB-GAM) in Hippocampal LTP and Spatial Learning Revealed by Studies on Overexpressing and Knockout Mice (Title, p. 330)\n\n20/4/2018 Pim\n- Species of over-expressed PTN_MOUSE, Pleiotrophin, Heparin-binding growth-associated molecule (HB-GAM) Heparin-binding neutrophic factor; Osteoblast-specific factor 1 is not stated in the publication. Species was traced back to rat via PMID:217035: \"l rats as described (6). The purified mRNA was used to synthesize cDNA with a random primer method (cDNA synthesis kit of Amersham Corp.).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3072" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

